OL,3,CItaly's 1990 World Cup star Salvatore
OL,4,CSchillaci dies aged 59
OL,6,FSalvatore 'Toto' Schillaci, the star
OL,7,Fof Italy's home World Cup in 1990, has
OL,8,Fdied aged 59.
OL,10,FThe Italian Football Federation (FIGC)
OL,11,Fconfirmed Schillaci's death on
OL,12,FWednesday morning.
OL,14,FThe striker, who played for clubs
OL,15,FMessina, Juventus and Inter Milan, was
OL,16,Fdiagnosed with colon cancer in 2022.
OL,18,FGabriele Gravina, the president of the
OL,19,FFIGC, said: "His face was a symbol of
OL,20,Fshared joy (and) will forever remain a
OL,21,Fcommon heritage of Italian football.
